Senate Resolution 452
By: Senator Albers of the 56th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending RUMC Job Networking; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, since its founding in 1988, RUMC Job Networking, a ministry of Roswell
3 United Methodist Church, has provided invaluable support to job seekers throughout the
4 metro Atlanta area, helping individuals secure employment, change careers, and re-enter the
5 workforce; and
6 WHEREAS, this distinguished ministry has grown into one of the largest and most impactful
7 job networking programs in the United States, having served more than 90,000 individuals
8 through its comprehensive career development services and networking opportunities; and
9 WHEREAS, RUMC Job Networking meets every second and fourth Monday of the month,
10 offering a full seven-hour program supported by over 155 dedicated volunteers, including
11 business leaders, career coaches, human resources professionals, and recruiters; and
12 WHEREAS, the ministry's extensive workshops and services include resume reviews,
13 LinkedIn optimization, interview preparation, overcoming ageism in the job search, stress
14 management, and networking through the Industry Guide Program, all aimed at equipping
15 job seekers with the tools necessary for career success; and
