16 WHEREAS, RUMC Job Networking has additionally hosted numerous Mini-Job Fairs and
17 has welcomed employers to bi-monthly meetings, offering job seekers direct access to
18 employment opportunities and fostering a bridge between talented professionals and hiring
19 organizations; and
20 WHEREAS, the impact of RUMC Job Networking has been widely recognized, including
21 a brief 2010 feature on Diane Sawyer's ABC World News Tonight and a two-hour special
22 hosted by Clark Howard on WSB-TV; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper to recognize RUMC Job Networking for its
24 unwavering commitment to empowering job seekers, strengthening communities, and
25 fostering professional growth.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
27 recognize and commend RUMC Job Networking for its decades of service and dedication
28 on behalf of job seekers in the State of Georgia and beyond as well as extend best wishes for
29 its continued success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
31 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to RUMC Job
32 Networking.
